		<hr size="1">Entaro Adun!!</P><P>The Zerglings destroyed your homeworld!! LoL</P><P>Anywho, </P><P>Whether you are going to stay with EQ1 or go to EQ2, the point is pretty moot: if you all read up on the news, SOE is offering people full access to almost all their online games for one monthly price of $20 bucks. That includes EQ, Planetside, station games, it will include EQ2 and I probably missed a few in there. (however, it sadly will not include SWG). </P><P>Now you can have it both ways!</P><P>With this, I really don't think EQ will die. </P><P>People will be drawn to EQ2 that never played EQ. For newby zones, these people are likely to see what EQ was like and begin a character here as well. For the upper lvl people, they won't lose their character and can come on at any time to raid that mob boss. </P><P>I think this is going to be the breakdown:</P><P>25% more people will be attracted to eq in general. That's a lot of people. </P><P>Now, with current players, I think about 30% are going to stick with ONLY eq. I think about half are going to go both ways, with equal proportions of those who would primarily do one or the other. The other 20% will probably leave eq and all those drOOdz can hunt EQ2's hill giants so I can have more :p</P><P>________________</P><P>Personally, I think this is kind of stupid IMHO. I mean, eq2 does look cool, but for anyone looking for something new: You're hunting the SAME Ol'Orc. Your living on the same ol'antonica. it's still Norrath. The charm will never match EQ's, and it will wear even sooner. </P><P>This isn't something fresh and original. </P><P>That doesn't mean that I won't test it out, now that I can keep my character. However, its at least a year down the road. They say its a year, but they haven't even put it out on BETA. I think any game needs at least a year of beta before they put it on the shelves. Because SOE isn't, there's only going to be more bugs. Don't be surprised if it ends up like Shadowbane, people couldn't even SIGN UP FOR IT!! (there was a bug preventing them! hahaha). </P><P>EQ isn't going anywhere for at least 2 or 3 years, and I wouldn't be surprised to see it last a lot longer than that. Remember people, this is a franchise. It's the Walt Disney of MMMORGPs, and people keep seeing those lousy movies no matter how stupid they are. And EQ isn't even stupid, its a pretty good product and a game that even kept you, Entaro Adun, playing for at least 3 years. Not many things would be able to hold your attention that long. Heck, half the world doesn't know how to play chess because they never had the patience to learn :p</P><P>Enjoy EQ, enjoy EQ2 if that's where the future will take you. Personally, after all the bugs are out, I think I'll enjoy both. </P><P>And Lionhearted will someday be able to hit lvl 65!! mwahaha. </P><P>Oh, BTW, they're not ignoring EQ 1 either. There are 2 more expansions in the works. Think SOE still wants to lose its millions of customers?<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
